In c++,
String is specified in double quotes,whereas char is stored within single quotes('')
Time Complexity is (TC!=time taken) 
->The rate at which the time taken increases w.r.to input size.
it is specified in Big O Notation -> O() (Upper Bound or worst case complexity)
time complexity is always computated based on worst case,avoid constants and avoid lower values
Best Case,Average Case,Worst Case
Space Complexity -> memory space where a program take.(Auxilary space + Input space).
PATTERNS:
* * *
* * *
* * *
code:
void nForest(int n) {
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
	{
		for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
		{
			cout<<"*"<<" ";
		}
		cout<<endl;
	}
}
* 
* *
* * *
Code:
void nForest(int n) {
	// Write your code here.
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		for(int j=0;j<=i;j++){
			cout<<"* ";
		}
		cout<<endl;
	}
}
